<answer>Parameterize the line segmented by variables $x$ and $y$ by $P=(x,y,0).$  The distance ${k}$ from $P$ to the plane $4x-7y+4z=25$ is given by
\[ k = k(P) = \frac{4x-7y+0-25}{\sqrt{4^2+7^2+4^2}} = \frac{4x-7y-25}{\sqrt{16+49+16}} = \frac{4x-7y-25}{\sqrt{81}} = \frac{4x-7y-25}{9}. \]
Now, we see that the square lies on the plane $z=1,$ so the cross-sectional area is the area of a circle with radius
\[ r = \frac{4x-7y-25}{9} \cdot \frac{1}{\sqrt{16+(-7)^2+4^2}} = \frac{4x-7y-25}{9\cdot \sqrt{16+49+16}} = \frac{4x-7y-25}{9\cdot \sqrt{81}} = \frac{4x-7y-25}{81}, \] which gives a maximal cross-sectional area of \[ \pi r^2 = \pi \left( \frac{4x-7y-25}{81} \right)^2 = \boxed{\frac{\pi}{6561} (4x-7y-25)^2}. \qedhere \] [/answer]

